1.)Clone the repository or create a new folder:
Download the files or create the project structure as outlined above.
2.)For Static Version:
Open the index.html file directly in your web browser.
3.)For Node.js Version (Optional Backend):
Ensure that you have Node.js installed.
4.)In the terminal, run the following command to install dependencies:
npm install express
5.)Start the server by running:
node server.js
6.)Open your browser and go to http://localhost:3000 to view the website.
